    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-11-17T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-11-17T00:00:00-05:00" n="336"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d336">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">
                    <gloss target="#t_CFM1">C.F.M.</gloss> Files: Lot M–88: Box 2079: <gloss
                        target="#t_CFM1">CFM</gloss> Documents</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Proposals by the <gloss type="from">Soviet Delegation</gloss>
                        to the <gloss type="to">Council of Foreign Ministers</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="37" xml:id="d336fn37">This paper was considered by the Council of
                        Foreign Ministers at its 4th and 5th Informal Meetings, November 20 and
                        November 21; for the United States Delegation Minutes of those meetings, see
                            <ref target="#pg_1200">pp. 1200</ref> and <ref target="#pg_1215"
                            >1215</ref>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <gloss target="#t_CFM46NY1">CFM(46) (NY)</gloss> 15 Revised<note n="38"
                            xml:id="d336fn38">This paper is virtually identical with the original
                            draft (<gloss target="#t_CFM46NY1">CFM(46)(NY)</gloss> 15, November 17,
                            1946), except for a slight revision in sub-paragraph <hi rend="italic"
                                >d</hi>.</note>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">New York</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-11-17">November 17,
                            1946</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p rend="center">
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Peace Treaty With Italy</hi>
                </p>
                <p rend="center">
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Article</hi> 16</p>
                <p rend="center">
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">amendments of soviet delegation to paragraph 11 of the
                        french proposal</hi>
                    <note n="39" xml:id="d336fn39">The paragraph under reference is that of the
                        French proposal for article 16 of the Draft Peace Treaty with Italy as
                        included in the Record of Recommendations of the Peace Conference, <ref
                            target="frus1946v04#pg_895">vol. <hi rend="smallcaps">iv</hi>, p.
                            895</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <p>11. <hi rend="italic">Free Port and Economic Questions</hi>
                </p>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="italic">Paragraph 11a</hi>)—accept draft of United States and United
                    Kingdom Delegations (see Article 30 of draft provisions for Free Port) with the
                    following changes: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“<hi rend="italic">a</hi>. A Free Port shall be established in the Free
                            Territory and shall be administered on the basis of the provisions of an
                            international instrument <hi rend="italic">drawn up by the Council of
                                Foreign Ministers and approved by the Security Council</hi>. (omit
                            words “controlling the Free Port of Trieste”)</p>
                        <p>The Government of the Free Territory shall enact all necessary
                            legislation and take all necessary steps to implement the provisions of
                            such instrument.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="italic">Paragraph 11b</hi>)—accept the draft of the French Delegations
                    with the following changes: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“<hi rend="italic">b</hi>) The establishment of free zones under the
                            exclusive jurisdiction of any country, <hi rend="italic">with the
                                exception of neighboring countries</hi>, is incompatible with the
                            Statute of the Free Territory and of the Free Port.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="italic">Paragraphs 11c</hi>) <hi rend="italic">and d</hi>)—Paragraph
                        11<hi rend="italic">c</hi> is accepted without amendment provided the
                    following wording is adopted for Paragraph 11<hi rend="italic">d</hi>).</p>
                <quote rend="blockquote">
                    <p>“<hi rend="italic">d</hi>) In order to enesure favorable conditions for the
                        economic development of the Free Territory of Trieste economic collaboration
                        shall be established between the Free Territory and Yugoslavia (customs
                        union, joint administration of the railroads of the Free Territory of
                        Trieste, etc.)”</p>
                </quote>
            </div>
